{
  "title": "The Bridegroom Soon Will Call Us",
  "key": "G major",
  "key_root": "G",
  "mode": "major",
  "meter": "3/4",
  "bpm": 100,
  "words": "Johann Walther, 1552",
  "music": "or &#39;Ich will ein Neues Singen&#39; or &#39;Praetorius 7&#39; from Musae Sionae, 1855",
  "tune": "Act Gott Vom Himmelreiche",
  "lyrics": {
    "v1": "The Bridegroom soon will call us, Come, all ye wedding guests! May not His voice appall us, While slumber binds our breasts; May all our lamps be burning, And oil be found in store, That we, with Him returning, May open find the door.",
    "v2": "There shall we see delighted Our dear Redeemer&#39;s face, Who leads our souls benighted To glory by His grace; The patriarchs shall meet us, The prophets&#39; holy band, Apostles, martyrs, greet us In that celestial land.",
    "v3": "They will not blush to own us As brothers, sisters dear, Love ever will be shown us When we with them appear; We all shall come before Him, Who for us Man became, As Lord and God adore Him, And ever bless His Name.",
    "v4": "Our Father, rich in blessing, Will give us crowns of gold And, to His bosom pressing, Impart a bliss untold, Will welcome with embraces Of never ending love, And deck us with His graces In blissful realms above.",
    "v5": "In yonder home shall never Be silent music&#39;s voice; With hearts and lips forever We shall in God rejoice; The angels shall adore Him, All saints shall sing His praise, And bring with joy before Him Their sweetest heav&#39;nly lays."
  },
